  In this paper, some of the main known results relative to the Vehicle Routing Problem are surveyed. The paper is organized as follows: (1) definition; (2) exact algorithms; (3) heuristic algorithms; (4) conclusion. Keywords Vehicle Routing Problem ; survey Agarwal et al., 1989 Y. Agarwal, K. Mathur, H.M. Salkin A set-partitioning-based algorithm for the vehicle routing problem Networks, 19 (1989), pp. 731–750 Balinski and Quandt, 1964 M. Balinski, R. Quandt On an integer program for a delivery problem Operations Research, 12 (1964), pp. 300–304 Benders, 1962 J.F. Benders Partitioning procedures for solving mixed-variables programming problems Numerische Mathematik, 4 (1962), pp. 238–252 Bodin et al., 1983 L.D. Bodin, B.L. Golden, A.A. Assad, M.O. Ball Routing and scheduling of vehicles and crews. The state of the art Computers and Operations Research, 10 (1983), pp. 69–211 Christofides, 1985a N. Christofides Vehicle routing E.L. Lawler, J.K. Lenstra, A.H.G. Rinnooy Kan, D.B. Shmoys (Eds.), The Traveling Salesman Problem. A Guided Tour of Combinatorial Optimization, Wiley, Chichester (1985), pp. 431–448 Christofides, 1985b N. Christofides Vehicle scheduling and routing 12th International Symposium on Mathematical Programming, Cambridge, MA (1985) Presented at the Christofides et al., 1979 N. Christofides, A. Mingozzi, P. Toth The vehicle routing problem N. Christofides, A. Mingozzi, P. Toth, C. Sandi (Eds.), Combinatorial Optimization, Wiley, Chichester (1979), pp. 315–338 Christofides et al., 1981a N. Christofides, A. Mingozzi, P. Toth Exact algorithms for the vehicle routing problem, based on spanning tree and shortest path relaxations Mathematical Programming, 20 (1981), pp. 255–282 Christofides et al., 1981b N. Christofides, A. Mingozzi, P. Toth State space relaxation procedures for the computation of bounds to routing problems Networks, 11 (1981), pp. 145–164 Clarke and Wright, 1964 G. Clarke, J.W. Wright Scheduling of vehicles from a central depot to a number